# Workflow Subgraph Determinism

## Source of truth

- For UUID wrapper nodes, the embedded definition under `definitions.subgraphs` is the source of truth for input/output ports.
- Wrapper `nodes[].inputs` and `nodes[].outputs` must match subgraph interface count and types.

## Required gates after mutation

- `python scripts/validate_workflow_json.py <path>`
- `python scripts/validate_workflow_topology.py <path>`

Recommended full pass:

- `python scripts/validate_workflow_json.py --semantics --topology <path>`

## Safe repair path (no guessing)

Use:

`python scripts/sync_subgraph_wrapper_ports.py <path> --subgraph-id <uuid> --write`

Then apply behavior wiring edits intentionally and re-run gates.

## Hard prohibitions

- No invented node types or unknown slot wiring.
- No silent link-id churn across unrelated nodes.
- No edits to unrelated subgraphs in the same file unless requested.
